      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T17:06:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "ok, i can try to adjust it on the C side as well to put the macros on both the declaration and the definition.\n\nAs a result of that change some things can come out of `config.h.in` and go into a header `_abi_annotation.h` which can then has to included by all libpldm and libpldm++ headers and implementation files.\n\nForgetting to include that header in some other header would then cause a build failure for library users which is a tradeoff, in the existing implementation there is no need to be careful there since the ABI macros are provided by `config.h`.\n\nAlso there would be a problem since a mismatch between header and source is possible.\n\nI explored this possible rework in https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/libpldm/+/88254",
